cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about a visual recognition dataset for plankton classification, which involves image processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses relevant metrics for evaluation of classification performance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) indicates that it could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the paper mentions the challenge of automated classification, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
